"{\"uid\": \"reason.com-2024-07-26-this-revolutionary-robotic-suit-enabled-a-paralyzed-man-to-carry-the-olympic-torch\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Log In  Create new account  Olympics  Eric Boehm|7.26.2024 4:00 PM  If Kevin Piette ever had any dreams of making it to the Olympics, they likely ended when the young tennis player was paralyzed in a motorcycle accident more than a decade ago.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 43, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Boehm\", \"score\": 0.8041144613200897, \"rank\": 0.24360404691968224, \"text\": \"Boehm\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Boehm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Boehm\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This week, however, Piette walked through the streets of Paris while carrying the Olympic flame-thanks to a genuinelyawesomerobotic exoskeleton.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999997814939, \"rank\": 2.1848556954474917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The video pretty much tells the whole story, so please enjoy:  Kevin Piette, paraplegic since an accident, made history today by carrying the Olympic flame with his exoskeleton!\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"?\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"???\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"pic.twitter.com/oejQHQRAwG  - Kevin W. (@Brink_Thinker)July 23, 2024    According to the Olympics'official website, the 36-year-old Piette is one of the first test \\\"pilots\\\" for these exoskeleton suits, which are currently being used for rehab but might soon be available for personal use.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Piette has taken part in \\\"cybathlons\\\"-competitions \\\"in which people with disabilities use assistive technologies to carry out everyday activities.\\\"\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 1011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wandercraft, the French-based company thatdevelopedthe \\\"Atalante X\\\" exo-suit Piette wears,saysits design is \\\"the first and only self-stabilizing exoskeleton in the market for personal everyday use to help impaired people walk hands free in their own communities.\\\"\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since gaining approval from the European Union's health regulators in 2019, Wandercraft says its devices have been used to help over 650 patients across over 5,000 sessions.\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999881766, \"rank\": 1.180410590906177e-11, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The companyreceived approval from the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) in 2022to use the exoskeleton suit for stroke rehabilitation in the U.S. and has opened a new headquartersin New York City.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_and_Drug_Administration\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.910905783660879e-34, \"text\": \"FDA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_and_Drug_Administration\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_and_Drug_Administration\"}, {\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powered_exoskeleton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"exoskeleton suit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powered_exoskeleton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powered_exoskeleton\"}, {\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.964235813991457e-14, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company was co-founded by Jean-Louis Constanza, whose son was suffering from neuropathy and slowly losing the ability to walk.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\", \"score\": 0.881383199962492, \"rank\": 0.1308980213089845, \"text\": \"Constanza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When he was five years old, I gave him his first wheelchair and told him I was a robotics engineer and he said I should make a robot that would allow him to walk,\\\" Constanzatolde-Magazine,\\u00a0which covers medical innovation, in 2022.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If that does not hit you right in the feels, then check out how Constanzadescribesusers' reactions to wearing his device for the first time: \\\"It is the moment of standing up with nothing in front of them to stop them falling that makes them laugh or cry-it is always a shock.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The act of walking is then a continued exhilaration.\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Standing in our exoskeleton is not like being verticalized in a frame or standing up in crutches, it is like becoming yourself again.\\\"\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2362, \"end\": 2373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powered_exoskeleton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0281544368275597e-17, \"text\": \"exoskeleton\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powered_exoskeleton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powered_exoskeleton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are meant to celebrate outstanding achievements in physical competition.\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Piette's participation in the torch relay certainly qualifies.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But let us save some cheers for the incredible human ingenuity behind Wandercraft's robo-suits-including Constanza, as well as his teams of engineers-that has taken an idea that seems like science fiction and turned it into reality.\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\", \"score\": 0.881383199962492, \"rank\": 0.1308980213089845, \"text\": \"Constanza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not wait to see people using these exoskeletons to get around American cities.\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999684646359, \"rank\": 2.609590961505058e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not screw this up, FDA!\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 2975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Start your day withReason.\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 3003, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get a daily brief of the most important stories and trends every weekday morning when you subscribe toReason Roundup.\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3113, \"end\": 3120, \"title\": \"